Title: Valor spark generator
Description: This Valor 5122420 spark generator is suitable for a wide selection of appliances, including those in the Icon, Dream and Visage ranges. A spark generator and spark electrode are part of a boiler's pilot assembly, used when generating a spark to ignite the pilot burner. This assembly is operated by an electronic control, usually via the user control panel but sometimes, particularly with older boilers, the pilot must be ignited manually.

Title: Valor 3002988 pilot unit
Description: This Valor 3002988 pilot unit is suitable for a variety of appliances, including those in the Visage, Dream and Icon ranges.  The pilot is the flame used to ignite gas entering the main burner. Gas is released into the burner via the gas valve when an appliance is switched on and ignited to begin the heating process. The pilot flame and printed circuit board (PCB) work together to make sure ignition is safe and efficient.

Title: Parts 061707 deaerator
Description: This automatic air vent is a spare part for use in the pump section of Vaillant VCWF, VKS, VUW, VU, VUI, VM, VMW, VMI, VCF, VC, VUWT4 and VSC appliances.  A central heating safety device, the air vent releases built up air. As water flows through the system, a float opens or closes the vent depending on the water level. When the system is full the float is pushed to the top, closing the vent until the water level drops. Title: Valor micro switch
Description: This Valor 540959 microswitch is suitable for use in a variety of appliances. The microswitch reacts to certain stimuli by performing a predetermined action, for example a microswitch in a hydraulic diverter valve will turn on in reaction to a connected tap being turned. The microswitch communicates the need for further hot water to the PCB (printed circuit board), which in turn initiates the hot water sequence. Various types of microswitch are available and should be chosen based on their intended location and the mechanism they are involved in.
